# BucketList Card

## Summary
The `BucketList` card is a custom Boxel card that allows users to create and manage a list of items, similar to a bucket list. It includes a header with the list name and the number of items, as well as a reusable `ChipsEditor` component that enables users to add, edit, and remove items in the list.

## Import
```javascript
import { BucketList } from '../bucket-list';
```

## Usage as a Field
To use the `BucketList` card as a field within a consuming card or field, you can include it in the `fields` section of your card definition:

```javascript
import { CardDef, field, contains } from '@cardstack/core';
import { BucketList } from '../bucket-list';

class MyCard extends CardDef {
  @field('bucket-list') bucketList = contains(BucketList);
}
```

In this example, the `BucketList` card is included as a field named `bucket-list` within the `MyCard` definition.

## Template Usage
To display the `BucketList` card within a consuming card or field, you can use the following template syntax:

```html
<@fields.bucket-list />
```

This will render the `BucketList` card and its associated `ChipsEditor` component.
